  "texts": [
    "The right plot reveals that increasing tree level has minimal effect on total MLFMA runtime, but decreasing the level significantly degrades performance.",
    "It suggests that we must focus on improving the less dense tree since the redundancy cant level up the speedup significantly from 0.4 to at east 1.",
    "The dominance of the near-field operator increases with box size (t), however, in denser trees (larger t) the fraction of time spent in near-field computation is already high, and the baseline implementation is welloptimized, leaving little chance for improvement via redundancy.",
